<h2>Detailed Specification</h2>

<h3>Design</h3>

<ul>
    <li>A Form Field is composed of the label, the input control and the error message component.</li>
    <li>The input control contained within the form field tags can be any simple reactive form control.</li>
    <li>The form field is designed to contain only one input control at a time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Code</h3>

<ul>
    <li>To customize the text for the label, set the <span class="code">label</span> property to desired text.</li>
    <li>The property <span class="code">for</span> needs to be set in order to link the label to the input control properly for accessibility.</li>
    <li>The property <span class="code">required</span> can be set in order to turn on the required validation and to show the red asterisk next to the label to indicate that the field is required.</li>
    <li>In order to override or specify messages for custom validation errors the <span class="code">messageConfig</span> property needs to be set
      containing an object with the validator key and the error message that you want to show for the validation error.
          {% highlight "html" %}
               [messageConfig]="{'required': '\'Field 1\' is required.'}"
          {% endhighlight %}
    </li>
    <li>The input control needs to have the <span class="code">formInput</span> directive so that the component knows which control to check for errors and to check if the component needs to be disabled.
          {% highlight "html" %}
              <form-field label="Field 1" for="field1" [messageConfig]="{'required': '\'Field 1\' is required.'}" required="required">
                <input type="text" formInput id="field1" class="jazz-input" placeholder="Enter Field 1 Here"
                       [class.jazz-input--error]="form.get('field1').invalid && (form.get('field1').dirty || form.get('field1').touched)"
                       formControlName="field1" required />
              </form-field>
          {% endhighlight %}
    </li>
</ul>

