<h3>States</h3>

<h4>Default</h4>
<p>The Default state of a Form Field is Empty and not in the Error state.</p>
<h4>Error (Warning/Invalid)</h4>
<p>The Error state of a Form Field indicates that the Form Field’s child input values are not value and optionally provides an error message that indicates the specific problem with the field.</p>
<h4>Correct</h4>
<p>The Correct state indicates that the Form Field’s child input values are correct/valid.  In most cases, this state would not need to be represented, but it may be useful in cases where achieving the correct value is difficult.</p>
<h4>Required</h4>
<p>The Required state indicates that a Form Field is required, meaning that a value must be specified for the inputs in that Form Field before the value can be accepted.</p>
