<h4>One (Single, Only)</h4>
<p>The One state for a Text Input indicates that a value has been provided for the input.  Any placeholders are usually hidden once a value has been provided.</p>
<h4>Overflow</h4>
<p>The Overflow state for a Text Input would be when the value specified for the component exceeds the available space to display that value.  By default, HTML Form inputs will truncate the display of any content that exceeds the available width, while preserving the underlying value.</p>

